verbose_text: A similar negative relationship was also found between the persistence of AF and levels of hs-IL-6, although baseline levels of hs-IL-6 were highest in patients with paroxysmal AF (2.71, 2.96, 2.36, and 2.03 pg/mL for first diagnosed, paroxysmal, persistent, and long standing persistent AF, respectively, p < 0.001; XREF_FIG [D-dimer only] and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
